    "body": "> none of those symbols are on users keyboards\n\nSymbol show only on mac, and are on mac keyboard: \n![photo](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/335567/5560871/07d62078-8db1-11e4-8d7e-a9b38f1e544c.JPG)\n\n> and are far from universally recognized\n\nAre everywhere and the standard on OS X menu\n\n![capture d ecran 2014-12-27 a 10 10 05](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/335567/5560874/356c3450-8db1-11e4-84c6-2e7b88db3f40.png)\n\n> Also, using upper case letters is confusing as some users will think they need to use shift for those.\n\nThis is standard on OS X Menu too, cf above screenshot and Apple Human interface guideline.\n"
