    "updated_at": "2014-12-27T15:29:39Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "As someone who used OSX for a long time, I would immediately recognize the symbols for Command, and Shift.  Control and Alt I recognize, but I have to spend a few seconds remembering which is which.  The rest of them I had to think about longer, particularly Return, which I thought was Backspace for a while.  I don't think I've ever see the symbol for Escape before.\n\nI suspect that a lot of less technical users would recognize very few of the sigils.\n"
