    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I can admit that backspace is one of the one I see rarely, but return (hookarrow) and enter (caret with flat hat) are both on my physical keyboard. \n\nEscape is in force quit among other, ctrl (^) is in special chars dialog, past without style, and full screen/presentation mode (no toolbar) often.\n![capture d ecran 2014-12-27 a 20 21 07](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/335567/5562132/fd986b34-8e05-11e4-83b5-7ca865c5154c.png)\n\nAnd sadly most of the user I know are mixing fn/alt  and ctrl/cmd  when they see it written in full letters. The 2 first pairs entering the category of : \"the ones I don't know what they are doing and that I never use\",  and the second pairs \"the one that start with a C\".\n"
  },
